<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52f5bbe6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s3907"><num value="3907">§ 3907.</num><heading> Other judicial review prohibited</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as expressly authorized by this chapter and chapter 5 of title 3, the compliance or noncompliance with the provisions of chapter 5 of title 3, and any action taken pursuant to chapter 5 of title 3, shall not be subject to judicial review.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52f5bbe7-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/331/s3/c">Pub. L. 104–331, § 3(c)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-26">Oct. 26, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/4071">110 Stat. 4071</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52f5bbe8-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id52f5bbe9-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id52f5bbea-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1997-10-01">Oct. 1, 1997</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/104/331/s3/d">section 3(d) of Pub. L. 104–331</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s1296">section 1296 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
